{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrx/pullrequests/221/comments/137257873.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrx/pull-requests/221/_/diff#comment-137257873"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 221, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrx/pullrequests/221.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrx/pull-requests/221"}}, "title": "Camera optical frame"}, "content": {"raw": "Hi @{5b9791e8a9fd6d2c834b5864} , I had some time to look into this. I took some pictures of the `front_left_camera_link` and `front_left_camera_link_optical` in RViz. I compared these observed frames with the expected ones according to [ROS rep-0103](https://www.ros.org/reps/rep-0103.html).\n\n![](data/bitbucket.org/repo/BgXLzgM/images/151616584-left_camera_link.png)\n![](data/bitbucket.org/repo/BgXLzgM/images/1982150883-left_camera_link_optical.png)\nSome relevant info from the PEP:\n\n```\n== Axis Orientation ==\nIn relation to a body the standard is:\n\nx forward\ny left\nz up\n\n== Suffix Frames ==\nIn the case of cameras, there is often a second frame defined with a \"_optical\" suffix. This uses a slightly different convention:\n\nz forward\nx right\ny down\n```\n\nLooks good to me! Thanks for the patch!", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Hi <span class=\"ap-mention\" data-atlassian-id=\"5b9791e8a9fd6d2c834b5864\">@Jonathan Wheare</span> , I had some time to look into this. I took some pictures of the <code>front_left_camera_link</code> and <code>front_left_camera_link_optical</code> in RViz. I compared these observed frames with the expected ones according to <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://www.ros.org/reps/rep-0103.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">ROS rep-0103</a>.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/BgXLzgM/images/151616584-left_camera_link.png\" />\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"data/bitbucket.org/repo/BgXLzgM/images/1982150883-left_camera_link_optical.png\" />\nSome relevant info from the PEP:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>== Axis Orientation ==\nIn relation to a body the standard is:\n\nx forward\ny left\nz up\n\n== Suffix Frames ==\nIn the case of cameras, there is often a second frame defined with a &quot;_optical&quot; suffix. This uses a slightly different convention:\n\nz forward\nx right\ny down\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Looks good to me! Thanks for the patch!</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2020-02-24T21:46:17.328996+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/692bf15758111acaddae4da15a47f9e5d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCA-0.png"}}, "nickname": "caguero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4ded1ddf-947e-4154-bbd1-3dba24f1bdbd"}, "updated_on": "2020-02-24T21:46:17.344673+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 137257873}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrx/pullrequests/221/comments/137257967.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrx/pull-requests/221/_/diff#comment-137257967"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 221, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrx/pullrequests/221.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrx/pull-requests/221"}}, "title": "Camera optical frame"}, "content": {"raw": "Note: I\u2019ll create a separate PR and merge it with `default` adding a new changelog entry.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Note: I\u2019ll create a separate PR and merge it with <code>default</code> adding a new changelog entry.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2020-02-24T21:47:10.453456+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/692bf15758111acaddae4da15a47f9e5d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCA-0.png"}}, "nickname": "caguero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4ded1ddf-947e-4154-bbd1-3dba24f1bdbd"}, "updated_on": "2020-02-24T21:47:10.460132+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 137257967}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrx/pullrequests/221/comments/137269449.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrx/pull-requests/221/_/diff#comment-137269449"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 221, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrx/pullrequests/221.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrx/pull-requests/221"}}, "title": "Camera optical frame"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks Carlos. \n\nRegards,\n\nJonathan.\n\n\u200c", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks Carlos. </p>\n<p>Regards,</p>\n<p>Jonathan.</p>\n<p>\u200c</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2020-02-24T23:42:32.686986+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jonathan Wheare", "uuid": "{65043b9b-c505-4efe-852a-3d2393a0ee80}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B65043b9b-c505-4efe-852a-3d2393a0ee80%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B65043b9b-c505-4efe-852a-3d2393a0ee80%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/initials/JW-2.png"}}, "nickname": "Jonathan Wheare", "type": "user", "account_id": "5b9791e8a9fd6d2c834b5864"}, "updated_on": "2020-02-24T23:42:32.828969+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 137269449}], "page": 1, "size": 3}